hpicfXrrpMIB.name: hpicfXrrpMIB

revisions.description: Revision to add objects to support controlled failback feature for XRRP.

hpicfXrrpMIB.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfXrrpMIB.description: This MIB module contains the definitions of Managed Objects for the XRRP router - the device running HP proprietory version of the Virtual Router Redundancy Protocol (VRRP).

XrrpRouterId.name: XrrpRouterId
XrrpRouterId.description: A number which serves to uniquely identify a XRRP router within a domain.

hpicfXrrpVersion.name: hpicfXrrpVersion
hpicfXrrpVersion.description: This value identifies the particular version of the XRRP supported by this device.

hpicfXrrpAdminState.name: hpicfXrrpAdminState
hpicfXrrpAdminState.description: The administrative state of the XRRP protocol on the box.

hpicfXrrpDomain.name: hpicfXrrpDomain
hpicfXrrpDomain.description: Domain that this router is in. The router can only be in one domain. Routers in the same domain can fail-over for each other. Up to 2 routers that have common VLANs can use the same XRRP Domain.

hpicfXrrpRouterId.name: hpicfXrrpRouterId
hpicfXrrpRouterId.description: Unique number for this router within a given domain. The router number (in combination with a VLAN ID) is used as an identifier for an XRRP instance within a domain. Along with 'hpicfXrrpDomain' it is used to create the XRRP MAC address for the XRRP instance this router owns. No two routers in the same domain can have the same router number in the same level 2 switching fabric.

hpicfXrrpFailback.name: hpicfXrrpFailback
hpicfXrrpFailback.description: Delay a router must wait before it can reclaim control for the virtual router it owns after its VLANs have come back up. This prevents any crashing for intermittent failures.

hpicfXrrpTrapCntl.name: hpicfXrrpTrapCntl
hpicfXrrpTrapCntl.description: Indicates whether the XRRP-enabled router will generate SNMP traps for events defined in this MIB. The set bit means 'enabled'. - stateChange(0) This bit controls whether the notification trap is allowed to be send when virtual router changes the state. - masterState(1) This bit controls whether the notification trap is allowed to be send when virtual router transitions to the Master state. - authFailure(2) This bit controls whether the notification trap is allowed to be send when virtual router detects an authentication error.

hpicfXrrpInstancesTable.name: hpicfXrrpInstancesTable
hpicfXrrpInstancesTable.description: A table that contains operational characteristics of the virtual routers (XRRP instances) configured on this routing device. Currently on a given router for a given VLAN up to 2 instances can be supported (i.e. router can be the owner of one XRRP instance and backup up to one other). The theoretical maximum of XRRP instances on the router can be MAX_VLAN*2, currently it is limited to 512.

hpicfXrrpInstanceEntry.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceEntry
hpicfXrrpInstanceEntry.description: An entry (row) in the 'hpicfXrrpInstancesTable' containing the operational characteristics of the specific virtual router (XRRP instance) configured on this device.

hpicfXrrpInstanceRouterId.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceRouterId
hpicfXrrpInstanceRouterId.description: The router number which owns the virtual router interface (XRRP instance). In combination with 'hpicfXrrpInstanceVlanId' used as an index value to uniquely identify a row in the 'hpicfXrrpInstancesTable' table.

hpicfXrrpInstanceVlanId.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceVlanId
hpicfXrrpInstanceVlanId.description: The VLAN ID where the virtual router (XRRP instance) is running on. In combination with 'hpicfXrrpInstanceRouterId' is used as an index value to uniquely identify a row in the 'hpicfXrrpInstancesTable' table.

hpicfXrrpInstanceOperState.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceOperState
hpicfXrrpInstanceOperState.description: The current state of the virtual router (XRRP instance) configured on this device. This object has the following defined values: - `initialize', which indicates that the virtual router (XRRP instance) is waiting for a startup event. - `backup', which indicates that virtual router (XRRP instance) is monitoring the availability of the Master. - `master', which indicates that the given virtual router (XRRP instance) is forwarding packets for the IP addresses associated with it, i.e. is in the Master state. - 'vlandown', which indicates that the VLAN associated with this virtual router (XRRP instance) is in down state.

hpicfXrrpInstanceAuthType.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceAuthType
hpicfXrrpInstanceAuthType.description: Authentication type used for VRRP protocol exchanges between virtual routers. - 'noAuthentication' means that VRRP protocol exchanges are notauthenticated. - 'simpleTextPassword' means that exchanges are authenticated by a clear text password.

hpicfXrrpInstanceAuthKey.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceAuthKey
hpicfXrrpInstanceAuthKey.description: This is an authentication string that is used to authenticate encapsulated VRRP packets received from other routers the XRRP instance is composed. This value must be consistently defined across the routers that form this XRRP instance. When read, it always returns an Octet String of length zero.

hpicfXrrpInstanceAdvertiseInterval.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceAdvertiseInterval
hpicfXrrpInstanceAdvertiseInterval.description: This parameter defines the advertisement interval in seconds for XRRP packets sent out by the Master of the XRRP instance.

hpicfXrrpInstanceUpTime.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceUpTime
hpicfXrrpInstanceUpTime.description: This is the value of the `sysUpTime' object when the XRRP instance transitioned out of `initialized' state.

hpicfXrrpInstanceRowStatus.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceRowStatus
hpicfXrrpInstanceRowStatus.description: Status of the row in the 'hpicfXrrpInstancesTable'.

hpicfXrrpInstanceAssoIpAddrTable.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceAssoIpAddrTable
hpicfXrrpInstanceAssoIpAddrTable.description: This table contains IP addresses associated with virtual routers (XRRP instances) configured on this device.

hpicfXrrpInstanceAssoIpAddrEntry.name: hpicfXrrpInstanceAssoIpAddrEntry
hpicfXrrpInstanceAssoIpAddrEntry.description: An entry in the 'hpicfXrrpInstanceAssoIpAddrTable'. The number of rows will be equal the number of IP addresses backed up by the all XRRP instances on this device.

hpicfXrrpAssoIpAddr.name: hpicfXrrpAssoIpAddr
hpicfXrrpAssoIpAddr.description: The backed up IP address configured on the VLAN 'hpicfXrrpInstanceVlanId' of the router 'hpicfXrrpInstanceRouterId'.

hpicfXrrpAssoIpMask.name: hpicfXrrpAssoIpMask
hpicfXrrpAssoIpMask.description: The subnet mask for the IP address.

hpicfXrrpAssoRowStatus.name: hpicfXrrpAssoRowStatus
hpicfXrrpAssoRowStatus.description: The status of the row in 'hpicfXrrpInstanceAssoIpAddrTable'.

hpicfXrrpTransferControl.name: hpicfXrrpTransferControl
hpicfXrrpTransferControl.description: When this object is set to transferCtrl (1), it acts as a trigger to intimate XRRP of the transfer of control from one router to another. When read, this object always returns notransferCtrl (2).

hpicfXrrpInfiniteFailback.name: hpicfXrrpInfiniteFailback
hpicfXrrpInfiniteFailback.description: When this object is set to enable (1), it sets the XRRP router on infinite failback. On initialization, the default value is disable (2).

hpicfXrrpStatsXrrpMacAddress.name: hpicfXrrpStatsXrrpMacAddress
hpicfXrrpStatsXrrpMacAddress.description: MAC Address used for XRRP instances for which this router is the owner. Value is determined by XRRP domain and unique router number.

hpicfXrrpStatsMacAndMask.name: hpicfXrrpStatsMacAndMask
hpicfXrrpStatsMacAndMask.description: This value contains the current AND mask used by XRRP to determine which MAC addresses can be received for routing.

hpicfXrrpStatsPktsRcvd.name: hpicfXrrpStatsPktsRcvd
hpicfXrrpStatsPktsRcvd.description: This value contains the number of XRRP packets received by the router.

hpicfXrrpStatsNotDomainPktsReject.name: hpicfXrrpStatsNotDomainPktsReject
hpicfXrrpStatsNotDomainPktsReject.description: This value contains the number of XRRP packets received from the other domains.

hpicfXrrpStatsCheckSumPktsReject.name: hpicfXrrpStatsCheckSumPktsReject
hpicfXrrpStatsCheckSumPktsReject.description: This value contains the number of XRRP packets rejected due to checksum errors.

hpicfXrrpStatsBadValuePktsReject.name: hpicfXrrpStatsBadValuePktsReject
hpicfXrrpStatsBadValuePktsReject.description: This value contains the number of received XRRP packets with bad values.

hpicfXrrpStatsCorruptedPktsReject.name: hpicfXrrpStatsCorruptedPktsReject
hpicfXrrpStatsCorruptedPktsReject.description: This value contains the number of received XRRP packets that are too short.

hpicfXrrpStatsVersionErrorPktsReject.name: hpicfXrrpStatsVersionErrorPktsReject
hpicfXrrpStatsVersionErrorPktsReject.description: This value contains the number of received XRRP packets with wrong version number.

hpicfXrrpStatsBcastArpsXmtd.name: hpicfXrrpStatsBcastArpsXmtd
hpicfXrrpStatsBcastArpsXmtd.description: This value contains the number of broacast arps sent.

hpicfXrrpStatsUpTime.name: hpicfXrrpStatsUpTime
hpicfXrrpStatsUpTime.description: This is the value of the `sysUpTime' object when the XRRP protocol has been last enabled. Used to count elapsed time since last XRRP enable action.

hpicfXrrpStatsProtocolCreateTime.name: hpicfXrrpStatsProtocolCreateTime
hpicfXrrpStatsProtocolCreateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when XRRP protocol was last activated (initialized). This can be used for polling applications to detect discontinuity in the above statistics counters if protocol has been reinitialized between polls.

hpicfXrrpStatsInstancesTable.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstancesTable
hpicfXrrpStatsInstancesTable.description: A table that contains statistics information for the XRRP instances on the router.

hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceEntry.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceEntry
hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceEntry.description: Information about a specific XRRP instance.

hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePktsRcvd.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePktsRcvd
hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePktsRcvd.description: This value contains the number of XRRP packets received by the virtual router (XRRP instance).

hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePktsXmtd.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePktsXmtd
hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePktsXmtd.description: This value contains the number of XRRP packets transmitted by the virtual router (XRRP instance).

hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceVersionErrPkts.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceVersionErrPkts
hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceVersionErrPkts.description: This value contains the number of XRRP packets received by the virtual router (XRRP instance) with incompatible version value in either the XRRP or VRRP portion of the header.

hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePriorityZeroPktsRc.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePriorityZeroPktsRcvd
hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePriorityZeroPktsRc.description: This value contains the number of XRRP packets received with the priority set to 0 on the virtual router (i.e. the current master is giving up control).

hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePriorityZeroPktsXm.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePriorityZeroPktsXmtd
hpicfXrrpStatsInstancePriorityZeroPktsXm.description: This value contains the number of XRRP packets transmitted by the virtual router with the priority set to 0 (i.e. the virtual router is giving up control).

hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceMismatchedIpPkts.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceMismatchedIpPkts
hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceMismatchedIpPkts.description: This value contains the number of XRRP packets received by the virtual router with an unknown mismatched IP addresses. The Backup router will automatically accept the addresses from a router with a priority of 255 (i.e. the virtual router owner).

hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceAuthFailPktsReject.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceAuthFailPktsReject
hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceAuthFailPktsReject.description: This value contains the number of rejected by this virtual router XRRP packets due to authentication failure (i.e. mismatched passwords).

hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceIntervalMismatchPk.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceIntervalMismatchPkts
hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceIntervalMismatchPk.description: This value contains the number of XRRP packets with the advertisement interval is a mismatch. The receiving router will change to that of the transmitter but logs a warning.

hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceCreateTime.name: hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceCreateTime
hpicfXrrpStatsInstanceCreateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this virtual router entry was last activated. This object allows to a management station to detect deletion and recreation cycles between polls and thus detect discontinuity in the above statistics counters.

hpicfXrrpStatsRcTable.name: hpicfXrrpStatsRcTable
hpicfXrrpStatsRcTable.description: A table that contains statistics information for virtual router coordinators in the domain.

hpicfXrrpStatsRcEntry.name: hpicfXrrpStatsRcEntry
hpicfXrrpStatsRcEntry.description: Information about a specific router coordinator.

hpicfXrrpStatsRcOperState.name: hpicfXrrpStatsRcOperState
hpicfXrrpStatsRcOperState.description: The current operational state of the router coordinator.

hpicfXrrpStatsRcType1PktsRcvd.name: hpicfXrrpStatsRcType1PktsRcvd
hpicfXrrpStatsRcType1PktsRcvd.description: This value contains the number of type 1 XRRP packets received by the router.

hpicfXrrpStatsRcType1PktsXmtd.name: hpicfXrrpStatsRcType1PktsXmtd
hpicfXrrpStatsRcType1PktsXmtd.description: This value contains the number of type 1 XRRP packets transmitted by the router.

hpicfXrrpStatsRcType2PktsRcvd.name: hpicfXrrpStatsRcType2PktsRcvd
hpicfXrrpStatsRcType2PktsRcvd.description: This value contains the number of type 2 XRRP packets received by the router.

hpicfXrrpStatsRcType2PktsXmtd.name: hpicfXrrpStatsRcType2PktsXmtd
hpicfXrrpStatsRcType2PktsXmtd.description: This value contains the number of type 2 XRRP packets transmitted by the router.

hpicfXrrpStatsRcBecomeMaster.name: hpicfXrrpStatsRcBecomeMaster
hpicfXrrpStatsRcBecomeMaster.description: The total number of times that this router has become a master.

hpicfXrrpStatsRcUnknownVlanId.name: hpicfXrrpStatsRcUnknownVlanId
hpicfXrrpStatsRcUnknownVlanId.description: The number of packets received by this virtual router that do not map to a known VLAN ID where an XRRP instance is supported.

hpicfXrrpStatsRcCreateTime.name: hpicfXrrpStatsRcCreateTime
hpicfXrrpStatsRcCreateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this router coordinator entry was last activated. This object allows to a management station to detect deletion and recreation cycles between polls and thus detect discontinuity in the above statistics counters.

hpicfXrrpTrapAuthErrorType.name: hpicfXrrpTrapAuthErrorType
hpicfXrrpTrapAuthErrorType.description: Potential types of configuration conflicts. Used by hpicfXrrpTrapAuthFailure trap.

hpicfXrrpTrapStateChange.name: hpicfXrrpTrapStateChange
hpicfXrrpTrapStateChange.description: This trap indicates that a XRRP router has changed state. The trap contains the domain number, the router coordinator number and state value for the change. This trap is being controlled by the state of 'hpicfXrrpTrapCntl' object.

hpicfXrrpTrapAuthFailure.name: hpicfXrrpTrapAuthFailure
hpicfXrrpTrapAuthFailure.description: This trap indicates that the authentication error occurred on a XRRP VLAN. The trap contains the domain number, this router number, instance id (owner router number and VLAN ID) that detected the error and type of the authentication error. This trap is being controlled by the state of 'hpicfXrrpTrapCntl' object.

hpicfXrrpMIBCompliance1.name: hpicfXrrpMIBCompliance1
hpicfXrrpMIBCompliance1.description: The core compliance statement for XRRP implementation.

hpicfXrrpMIBCompliance2.name: hpicfXrrpMIBCompliance2
hpicfXrrpMIBCompliance2.description: The core compliance statement for XRRP implementation.

hpicfXrrpTrapGroup.name: hpicfXrrpTrapGroup
hpicfXrrpTrapGroup.description: Conformance group for objects contained in XRRP notifications.
